<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,249,670]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,500,429,454]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Hypopygium description</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[520,664,429,454]" captionStart="FIGURES 59 – 62" captionStartId="26.[151,264,1967,1990]" captionTargetBox="[155,1431,530,1939]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[151,1436,518,1946]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURES 59 – 62. Coniceromyia convergens hypopygium, 59. Dorsal, 60. Ventral, 61. Left lateral, 62. Right lateral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1052930/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Figs. 59–62</figureCitation>
). Hypopygium light brown. Epandrium covered with microtrichia dorsally, with small proximal lateral areas bare; epandrial dorsal and left sutures present. Left epandrial process dorsally setose, with medial apically rounded projection near base, ventral lobe, subepandrial setose process near base and subepandrial transversal elevation. Right epandrial projection with subepandrial group of setulae. Hypoproct with three setae. Right lobe of hypandrium without projections.
</paragraph>
